Citation.sAbstract: Densities of aqueous solutions of malonic acid in the (0.01-1.0) mole kg 1 concentration range were measured at 5 K intervals, from 278.15 K to 343.15 K. These densities served to determine the apparent molar volumes. Changes of densities with temperature permitted evaluation of the cubic expansion coefficients and the derivatives of isobaric heat capacities with respect to pressure which are interrelated with the second derivatives of volume with respect to temperature. Thermal dependence of volumetric properties of aqueous solutions of malonic acid is examined in terms of changes in the structure of water.
Citation.sTitle: Volumetric properties of aqueous solutions of malonic acid
